snippet.textDisplay: This is undoubtedly a beautifully written song and Lewis Capaldi is one of the top male soloists in the U.K, but having heard Nicola Roberts cover version on the Masked singer recently, I actually prefer her version, she has tremendous vocal range and brings enormous emotion to this beautiful song, perhaps I'm slightly biased because I generally prefer female vocalists over male singers, because a lot of modern male singers tend to have raspy gravelly tone to their voice, which sounds good on rock tracks, but not so good on ballads.
snippet.textOriginal: This is undoubtedly a beautifully written song and Lewis Capaldi is one of the top male soloists in the U.K, but having heard Nicola Roberts cover version on the Masked singer recently, I actually prefer her version, she has tremendous vocal range and brings enormous emotion to this beautiful song, perhaps I'm slightly biased because I generally prefer female vocalists over male singers, because a lot of modern male singers tend to have raspy gravelly tone to their voice, which sounds good on rock tracks, but not so good on ballads.
